text.tspan: The source defines a terrorist attack as: "the threatened or actual use of illegal force and violence by a non-state
actor to attain a political, economic, religious, or social goal through fear, coercion, or intimidation." The perpetrators
of the incidents must be sub-national actors; data does not include acts of state terrorism.
